  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Medicine for Venezuela</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to the shortage of medications in Venezuela, the focus of this project is to supply basic medicines for distribution within Venezuela through a network of 23 local Lutheran congregations. The Lutheran Church of Venezuela, with the assistance of the Women&apos;s Society of the Lutheran Church of Venezuela, will gather a list of needed medications from Venezuela; the list will be sent to the Lutheran Church of Chile where the requested medicines will be purchased by the Program Manager with the assistance of a licensed pharmacist; the medicines with then be shipped via courier approximately every 30 days for distribution to the requesting congregations with the assistance of the Women&apos;s Society and ultimately to the beneficiaries with the assistance of the local Pastors or their designees. It is anticipated that in a 3 month period, the project has the potential to directly benefit 500+ individuals in Venezuela.</narrative>
  </description>
